            Born from a family recipe in the rolling hills of Tuscany, LITES began as a dream to share
            authentic Italian flavors with the world. Our founder's grandmother's handwritten recipes
            still guide our kitchen today. From slow-simmered ragù that takes 12 hours to perfect,
            to fresh mozzarella made every morning, we honor tradition while creating new memories.
            Every plate we serve carries the soul of Italy and the warmth of family.
        </p>
